>
  <section>
    <h2>What we cover</h2>
    <p>Consumer banking in the UAE — credit cards, salary transfers, the AECB credit bureau, customer-service patterns at the major issuers (FAB, ENBD, Mashreq, ADCB, HSBC, DIB, ADIB and others). Loyalty programmes — Skywards, Etihad Guest, Qatar Avios, flydubai OPEN, Air Arabia Airewards, hotel programmes operating in the UAE, and bank-proprietary points (FAB Rewards, ENBD Rewards, Mashreq Salaam, ADCB TouchPoints). Lifestyle deals tracked through Dubai Summer Surprises, Ramadan, and National Day cycles.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Interview requests</h2>
    <p>Email <a href="mailto:info@dubaipoints.ae?subject=Press">info@dubaipoints.ae</a> with subject "<em>Press</em>" and a brief on the topic, deadline and outlet. We aim to respond within one business day. We're available in English and conversational Arabic; for broadcast we can do remote (Riverside / Zoom) and Dubai-based in-studio with notice.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Quoting our work</h2>
    <p>Standard journalism citation rules apply. Reproduce up to two sentences with attribution and a link back to the source page. For broader use — full tables, valuation figures, syndication — email us first; in most cases we say yes for outlets covering UAE consumer finance.</p>
    <p>Our <a href="/valuations/">AED valuations</a> are an exception: the figures will be sampled methodically once the cadence begins (Q3 2026), and we'd prefer outlets cite the methodology page when reproducing the table so readers can read the caveats.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Editorial standards</h2>
    <p>Independence and AED-first reporting are foundational. We do not accept payment for coverage, do not pay sources, and do not run advertorial as editorial. The <a href="/editorial-policy/">editorial policy</a> spells out the verification standard. The <a href="/how-we-make-money/">how-we-make-money</a> page is the financial firewall.</p>
  </section>

